HEADWORD: Phanerocodonic
<hw>Phan`er*o*co*don"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fanero`s</grk> evident + <grk>kw`dwn</grk> a bell.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having an umbrella-shaped or bell-shaped body,
with a wide, open cavity beneath; -- said of certain
jellyfishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phanerocrystalline</ent>⟦br⟧
